tag.inscription: This Red Oak was planted on September 25, 2009 dedicated to the memory of Jeffrey Scott Hiatt whose life was taken while working on I-35 South on September 25, 2008. He is missed by so many.
tag.inscription_2: To plant a tree in memory of a loved one is not only a gift to the earth, but more importantly "A Legacy To The Future " for all those left behind.

tag.inscription: This maple was planted May 1, 1998 in memory of H. Ellwood (Woody) Watson, a dedicated and valued member of the Ames Parks and Recreation staff from 1963 - 1994.
Dear Lord, May this tree grow strong and beautiful and in all its strength and beauty bring Love and Peace to all the children while they Live, Laugh, Love and Play. Amen
tag.inscription_2: This tree was planted by the city of Ames in the memory of Spencer Lee Corson May 2, 2005 - June 24, 2008

tag.inscription: MIKE JACOBSEN AS THIS RED MAPLE GROWS, SO WILL OUR MEMORIES OF YOU. YOUR FRIENDS
